ZH: 他只是在附和我的话，他没有真正理解。
EN: He was just echoing my words, he didn't truly understand.

ZH: 她经常无条件地附和她的朋友。
EN: She often blindly agrees with her friends.

ZH: 我只是出于礼貌地附和他。
EN: I only echoed him out of politeness.

ZH: 他始终附和老师的观点。
EN: He always echoes the teacher's opinions.

ZH: 她总是附和她的上司，从不表达自己的意见。
EN: She always echoes her boss and never expresses her own opinions.

ZH: 我们需要员工们敢于提出自己的意见，而不仅仅是附和。
EN: We need employees who dare to voice their own opinions instead of just echoing.

ZH: 她附和了我一句，然后转身离开了。
EN: She echoed me with a single sentence and then walked away.

ZH: 我喜欢与那些能够提供新观点的人交流，而不只是附和我的想法。
EN: I enjoy conversing with people who can bring new perspectives rather than simply echoing my thoughts.

ZH: 他觉得自己的意见无足轻重，总是附和别人的意见。
EN: He feels his opinions are insignificant and always echoes others' opinions.

ZH: 这些政治家常常互相附和，而忽略了真正的问题。
EN: These politicians often echo each other and ignore the real issues.

ZH: 他经常附和自己的老板，以保持好感。
EN: He often echoes his boss to maintain a good relationship.

ZH: 这个团队需要有不同的意见，不仅是盲目附和。
EN: This team needs diverse opinions, not just blind echoing.

ZH: 附和并不总是错，有时候也可以帮助和睦相处。
EN: Echoing is not always wrong; sometimes it can help maintain harmony.

ZH: 她对待每个人的意见都只是附和，不过是想保持和睦。
EN: She simply echoes everyone's opinions to maintain peace.

ZH: 在团队中，每个人都应该自由表达自己的想法，而不是一味附和。
EN: In a team, everyone should freely express their ideas instead of blindly echoing.

ZH: 他只是为了讨好老板才会附和他的意见。
EN: He only echoes the boss's opinions to please him.

ZH: 我不喜欢被人盲目附和，我喜欢真实的讨论。
EN: I don't like being blindly echoed; I prefer genuine discussions.

ZH: 我不太赞同这个观点，但我会附和一下。
EN: I don't completely agree with this viewpoint, but I will echo it.

ZH: 这个政客总是附和选民的观点，以求得选举成功。
EN: This politician always echoes the voters' opinions in order to achieve electoral success.

ZH: 我不会仅仅因为他是我的朋友就一味附和他的意见。
EN: I won't blindly echo his opinions just because he is my friend.
